---
description: "Production Python 3.11+ standard тАФ strict typing, __slots__, exact-name imports, match/case, security hygiene"
---

# Python Pro Rules

## BANNED тАФ Never generate these

- `import json` / `import asyncio` / `import os` тАФ ALWAYS: `from json import loads`, `from asyncio import run`, `from os import environ`
- `from typing import Any` / `Optional` тАФ use `str | None` for nullable, precise types otherwise
- `import x` (full module imports) тАФ always `from x import y` (exact names)
- `== None` / `== True` тАФ use `is None` / `is True` or truthiness
- `except:` / `except Exception:` тАФ catch specific exceptions
- `def f(x=[])` тАФ mutable default args, use `None` + in-body init
- `eval` / `exec` / `shell=True` / `pickle.loads` on untrusted data
- `assert` outside tests тАФ `-O` strips it, raise explicitly instead

## REQUIRED тАФ Always generate these

- Shebang + path comment on every `.py` file: `#!/usr/bin/env python3` / `# filename.py тАФ description.`
- `from __future__ import annotations` at top
- Type annotations on ALL variables, parameters, returns: `x: int = 1`, `def f(x: str) -> int:`
- `__slots__` on ALL classes: `class Foo: __slots__ = ("x",)`
- `match/case` over `if/elif` for 3+ branches
- `ClassVar` for class constants, `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for module constants
- Docstrings: one-line imperative on public API only (PEP 257)
- `dataclass(slots=True)` for data containers
- `is None` / `is not None` тАФ never `==` comparison for None

## Style

- 88 char max line length
- `snake_case` for functions/vars, `PascalCase` for classes
- Acronyms fully capped: `HTTPClient`, not `HttpClient`
- `pathlib` over `os.path`
- Imports: stdlib тЖТ third-party тЖТ local (blank-line separated)
- No wildcard `from x import *`

## Security

- `secrets` (not `random`) for tokens
- `hashlib.sha256+` (never `md5`/`sha1`) for security hashing
- Parameterised SQL only тАФ no f-string queries
- `tempfile.mkstemp` (never `mktemp`)
- No hardcoded paths тАФ use `Path(__file__).parent`

## Testing

- `pytest` + `pytest-asyncio`
- Test every public function against empty/None/wrong-type/boundary inputs

## Architecture

- `cli/` тАФ single core powering CLI, MCP server, and hooks
- Pipeline: codemods тЖТ ruff --fix тЖТ black тЖТ lint тЖТ validator тЖТ security тЖТ complexity
- `skills/*.md` тАФ rule data, not loadable skills
